There he is.

50:32.333 --> 50:35.075
Hey! Ruddy! Ruddy!

50:35.119 --> 50:36.772
Get in the car.

50:36.816 --> 50:38.122
You okay?Get in the car!

50:38.165 --> 50:39.384
I've got a flight to catch.

50:39.427 --> 50:41.647
And, no, I'm not fucking okay.

50:41.690 --> 50:43.518
Hey.

50:44.345 --> 50:47.348
Bob, tell me,
what's going, man?

50:47.392 --> 50:48.784
The goddamn mafia
put a fucking rat

50:48.828 --> 50:50.612
in my fuckin' bed.

50:50.656 --> 50:52.527
A what?A fuckin' rat.

50:52.571 --> 50:55.487
Wrapped in your book,
"The Godfather."

50:55.530 --> 50:56.966
All right.
Look, just relax.

50:57.010 --> 50:59.708
Fuck you!
"Relax." Fuck you.

50:59.752 --> 51:01.232
I don't know what the fuck
you got me into,

51:01.275 --> 51:02.842
but I am not getting killed

51:02.885 --> 51:04.104
for some gangster movie,
all right?

51:04.148 --> 51:05.540
Now,
this is your fucking job.

51:05.584 --> 51:07.629
You deal with it
or I swear to God,

51:07.673 --> 51:10.763
I will shut this picture down,
understand?

51:10.806 --> 51:12.417
I mean, what was I thinking?I'm gonna handle it, okay?

51:12.460 --> 51:13.766
I'm gonna handle it.Good.

51:13.809 --> 51:15.768
You do that.

51:17.552 --> 51:20.251
Comfortable?
Get the fuck out of my car.

51:20.294 --> 51:21.556
I just wanted to make sure
you're okay.

51:21.600 --> 51:23.950
Get the fuck out.

51:23.993 --> 51:26.474
Fucking amateur.
Hit it, Michael.

51:41.533 --> 51:43.143
You look like shit.

51:43.187 --> 51:45.145
Still prettier than you,
bubbie.

51:45.189 --> 51:47.800
I'm assuming you haven't read
the trades today.

51:47.843 --> 51:50.063
Hmm? We're in trouble.

51:50.107 --> 51:51.456
Paramount being
on the losing team

51:51.499 --> 51:52.718
in Hollywood
is hardly a secret.

51:52.761 --> 51:53.936
You know,
"Variety" needs to find

51:53.980 --> 51:55.677
a new fucking story, man.

51:55.721 --> 51:58.245
Paramount's not the story.

51:58.289 --> 52:00.247
You are.

52:08.603 --> 52:11.737
Fucking Lapidus.

52:17.438 --> 52:20.746
How long have you been up?

52:20.789 --> 52:23.357
A little while.

52:25.707 --> 52:27.666
I need coffee.

52:27.709 --> 52:30.016
Why don't we get
breakfast sent up?

52:32.497 --> 52:34.368
Can't, baby. I gotta figure
this New York shit out

52:34.412 --> 52:37.502
if we're gonna shoot here.

52:37.545 --> 52:39.939
Would you at least get me
one of those croissant I like

52:39.982 --> 52:43.116
from the cart on the corner
before you desert me?

52:48.774 --> 52:52.038
You are at one of the nicest
hotels in the world

52:52.081 --> 52:53.996
and you want me
to get you a croissant

52:54.040 --> 52:55.998
from a cart on the street?

52:56.042 --> 52:57.826
Yes.

52:57.870 --> 53:00.742
That's my girl.

53:00.786 --> 53:02.962
I'm very fancy, you know.

53:03.005 --> 53:06.226
Yes, you are.
You are very fancy.

53:07.358 --> 53:09.490
And a coffee as well.And a coffee.

53:13.233 --> 53:14.539
Hey,
you're Al Ruddy, right?

53:14.582 --> 53:16.541
Yeah, look,
there's somebody important

53:16.584 --> 53:17.890
who wants to talk to you.

53:17.933 --> 53:19.544
Get in the car.

53:19.587 --> 53:21.372
Yeah, look, I'm a--
I'm a little busy right now.

53:22.764 --> 53:24.723
Get in the car.

53:26.420 --> 53:29.118
I'm not gonna ask you again.

53:47.006 --> 53:48.877
Take the bridge.

55:10.394 --> 55:11.395
What's Al hiding?

55:11.830 --> 55:13.048
There's something
heavy around him

55:13.092 --> 55:14.441
that he's not telling me.

55:14.485 --> 55:16.400
I'm not gonna sit here
and lie to you.

55:17.270 --> 55:19.228
I'm also not gonna say
anything if he hasn't.

55:19.272 --> 55:21.187
It was very important to us

55:21.230 --> 55:25.844
that in a story primarily
dominated by males,

55:25.887 --> 55:28.760
that the female characters
had their own agency

55:28.803 --> 55:31.371
and were not just props
in the men's story lines.

55:31.415 --> 55:32.633
Touché, mon amie.

55:35.549 --> 55:38.378
It was very important
to highlight

55:38.422 --> 55:40.772
how ahead of their time
these women were.

55:41.120 --> 55:43.340
I'm an ally, I'm just not yours.

55:43.383 --> 55:46.038
They succeeded in spite
of the challenges

55:46.081 --> 55:47.735
that were in front of them.

55:47.779 --> 55:49.215
I get why Al likes you.

55:49.258 --> 55:53.001
Bettye, I think ultimately
in my perception of it,

55:53.045 --> 55:55.613
she really handles herself
in a way

55:55.656 --> 55:57.615
that I think
is quite inspirational

55:57.658 --> 56:00.400
for past, present,
and future females

56:00.444 --> 56:01.836
because she does it with grace,

56:01.880 --> 56:04.404
and also I think she's
incredibly loyal.

56:04.448 --> 56:07.276
You see that with
the relationship
between her and Ruddy.

56:07.320 --> 56:08.930
I understand if you need to cut
and run.

56:09.496 --> 56:10.932
I'm not running either.

56:10.976 --> 56:12.369
Bettye was like
a relative of mine.

56:12.412 --> 56:13.674
And the minute I met her,

56:13.718 --> 56:15.110
I knew this was the right person
for me.

56:15.502 --> 56:16.982
So what's the move now then?

56:17.591 --> 56:19.506
This is Andrea Eastman,
Head of Casting.

56:19.550 --> 56:21.421
She's one of the only women

56:21.465 --> 56:23.597
that had such
a high power position.

56:23.641 --> 56:25.207
She's a big deal at Paramount.

56:25.251 --> 56:26.339
I agree.

56:26.383 --> 56:28.080
It was such a boys' club
back then.

56:28.123 --> 56:29.211
How do you know that?

56:29.255 --> 56:30.735
I thought it was
really well-written

56:30.778 --> 56:35.087
to show how she kind of
exerts herself in that world,

56:35.130 --> 56:37.959
and how she does it
in such a feminine way.

56:38.003 --> 56:39.526
She's really fun,

56:39.570 --> 56:42.268
and she shows it in her outfits
and her makeup and her hair.

56:42.311 --> 56:43.617
I don't know
how you stay comfortable

56:43.661 --> 56:44.923
in that skirt all day.

56:44.966 --> 56:46.403
It's a skirt, what's not
comfortable about it?

56:46.446 --> 56:47.926
I could talk about
that scene forever.

56:47.969 --> 56:49.841
I have so many good things
to say about that scene.

56:50.232 --> 56:52.191
I loved it, first and foremost,

56:52.234 --> 56:54.280
for the relationship
between Bettye and Andrea,

56:54.323 --> 56:56.064
how they're kind of
sussing each other out.

56:56.108 --> 56:59.590
So how'd you start working
with Ruddy?

56:59.633 --> 57:01.940
I've never seen an assistant
this involved in the process.

57:01.983 --> 57:04.246
We're both kind of like,
"Did you?"

57:04.290 --> 57:05.857
I didn't fuck him,
if that's what you're asking.

57:05.900 --> 57:08.599
They were two women that
are navigating the world

57:08.642 --> 57:10.557
in a very, very different way,

57:10.601 --> 57:13.430
but are still fierce
in their own right,

57:13.952 --> 57:17.216
not just because they were
women doing these jobs,

57:17.259 --> 57:20.306
but because they were
incredible people
doing these jobs.

57:20.349 --> 57:21.916
How did you
become head of casting?

57:21.960 --> 57:24.876
I like to think it's 'cause
I have a real eye for talent,

57:25.703 --> 57:27.748
but it might've been the skirt.
I don't know.

57:27.792 --> 57:29.184
That scene,

57:29.228 --> 57:31.448
I think it was supposed
to be in a casting office,

57:31.491 --> 57:34.363
and Dexter Fletcher was
like, "Oh no, no, no, no.

57:34.407 --> 57:35.974
We're gonna blow the scene out.

57:36.017 --> 57:38.193
It's gonna be driving
through the Paramount lot.

57:38.237 --> 57:41.458
There's gonna be welders,
there's gonna be gladiators."

57:41.501 --> 57:44.373
We got to zip around
the Paramount lot

57:44.417 --> 57:45.810
on a Sunday when it was empty.

57:45.853 --> 57:49.553
So you fully were transported
into their universe.

57:49.596 --> 57:50.989
It was a pinch-me moment.

57:51.032 --> 57:53.687
I just-- It makes all my hair
stand up, you know?

57:55.515 --> 57:57.125
We had another scene
where Coppola

57:57.169 --> 57:58.779
and Puzo were working
on the script.

57:58.823 --> 58:00.302
They were artists,
at the end of the day.

58:00.346 --> 58:04.089
They existed based on their
imagination.

58:04.132 --> 58:06.047
Telling stories,
creating a world.

58:06.657 --> 58:09.050
I'd just met Patrick
in rehearsal,

58:09.094 --> 58:11.618
and he was like, "Yeah, I'm
looking for a place to live."

58:11.662 --> 58:13.577
And I was like,

58:13.925 --> 58:15.317
all right, I'll take a risk here

58:15.361 --> 58:17.537
out of, you know,
the love of the game.

58:17.581 --> 58:19.365
Let's get method here, man.

58:19.408 --> 58:20.322
You never know.

58:20.758 --> 58:21.628
Fingers crossed, right?

58:23.108 --> 58:25.197
He was my roommate
for the first two

58:25.240 --> 58:26.459
or three weeks of shooting.

58:26.503 --> 58:28.243
It's not something
I will soon forget.

58:28.287 --> 58:31.290
That connection when you
meet someone
who you connect with,

58:31.333 --> 58:32.987
creatively and artistically,

58:33.031 --> 58:36.164
it's a rare thing
and it's a really special thing.

58:36.208 --> 58:37.470
Did you eat my ham?

58:37.514 --> 58:40.908
So I think that gave
such a wonderful rhythm

58:40.952 --> 58:42.910
to their relationship
very quickly.

58:43.389 --> 58:44.738
I'm loving you, Mario.

58:45.217 --> 58:47.001
And I think it shows,
I think that on the screen,

58:47.045 --> 58:49.221
you see that we genuinely
really get along.

58:49.264 --> 58:50.178
Salute.

58:51.658 --> 58:53.051
That was a big risk. He could
have been a real jerk...

58:53.094 --> 58:54.443
...you know,
but he was great, he was great.

58:54.487 --> 58:55.793
How lucky are we
to have been able

58:55.836 --> 58:57.490
to develop a relationship

58:58.012 --> 59:00.101
that is gonna effortlessly
bring itself to set?

59:00.449 --> 59:01.755
It's a beautiful gift.

59:01.799 --> 59:03.235
Hey, I want in on this.
